First of all, the burger was "absolutely phenomenal". It's without a doubt one of the best, if not the best burgers ever. However, there the cajun fries that we ordered were far from phenomenal. When we were offered cajun fries, my friend and I thought of popeyes fries, but the fries we got, while plentiful, were honestly just overly seasoned with what is probably prepackaged jerk seasoning that you can find in a supermarket. The spice covered every bit of the fries and it was very overpowering. The initial flavor was relatively pleasant but after eating multiple fries, it was too much and we ended up throwing out half our remaining fries when we left. Lastly, the restaurant atmosphere. When we sat down there were crumbs everywhere but the only people in the place were the workers. The tables were all pretty dirty so we brushed off the table we sat at. While we were eating, we couldn't help but notice the bland music playing on the speakers. It wasn't too loud or anything, just unpleasant music that would be irrelevant by pretty much anyone's standards. Overall, i give the experience 3 stars.
